What happens when a user logs into a computer? 
When a user logs into a computer, their device would usually be turned off. They would need to first power on the device. Sometimes, their devices would install updates for their operating systems. But, if there are no updates, the user would need to enter their credentials such as their username and password. Once they do, they will have access to their operating system. 
1. Power on their device 
2 (if needed). Allow for latest updates of operating system to take place
3. User enters their credentials (username and password)
4. User has access to their computer 
